value.title: McConnell says he would "absolutely" support Trump if he's the 2024 GOP nominee
value.excerpt: Just two weeks ago, the Senate Minority Leader called the former president "practically and morally responsible for provoking the events" of January 6.

value.title: Pelosi vows to keep minimum wage provision in House bill; Harris could act
value.excerpt: The Senate's chief parliamentarian ruled Thursday that a federal minimum wage hike should not be included in the $1.9 trillion COVID-19 relief package, but that seemed to do little to deter House Democrats from pursuing the plan — against impossible odds.

value.title: Donald Trump Jr.: Donald Trump is ‘still the future of the Republican Party’
value.excerpt: Former President Donald Trump is the future of the Republican Party, his eldest son Donald Trump Jr. argued on Thursday.

value.title: Cuomo jabs Trump vaccine effort amid NY governor's own snowballing controversies
value.excerpt: New York Gov. Andrew Cuomo on Thursday took shots at former President Donald Trump’s handling of the COVID-19 vaccine effort, as pressure on the governor mounts over sexual harassment claims and how he handled nursing home patient care in his state.

value.title: Rand Paul: Lot of ‘hypocrisy’ from Biden admin on immigration, migrant facilities
value.excerpt: The Biden administration is showing "hypocrisy" by reopening a migrant facility that the Trump administration was criticized for using, Sen. Rand Paul, R-Ky., said on Thursday.

value.title: Big Lie? Big Whoop: Many Republicans on Capitol Hill see little reason to bat down Trump's election lies
value.excerpt: The deadly January 6 insurrection in the Capitol may have caused many voters to recoil at former President Donald Trump's election lies.

value.title: Nikki Haley Iced Out Of CPAC After Underestimating Donald Trump's Influence
value.excerpt: The former ambassador hasn't been invited to speak, another blow to any presidential ambitions she may harbor.

value.title: Trump's pardon of Lil Wayne said to be the breaking point for 'QAnon Shaman' in new court documents filled with bizarre anecdotes
value.excerpt: An attorney for Jacob Chansley, the "QAnon Shaman," filed a pretrial release motion Tuesday, weeks after he charged in the Capitol riot.

value.title: Biden should not give up his sole nuclear authority, GOP lawmakers say
value.excerpt: Three Republican members of the House Armed Services Committee on Wednesday issued a statement pushing back on Democrats' letter to President Biden urging him to give up his sole nuclear authority.

value.title: Biden resets Saudi ties as US prepares to release intelligence report on Khashoggi's murder
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden's reset of the US-Saudi Arabia relationship will take another step with the release of a long-awaited US intelligence report on the killing of Saudi insider turned dissident Jamal Khashoggi.

value.title: Rick Scott calls for Biden's 'immediate attention' on moving 2022 Olympics from China
value.excerpt: Republican Sen. Rick Scott is requesting a meeting with President Biden and calling for his "immediate attention" to moving the 2022 Winter Olympic Games out of Beijing, citing China’s human rights abuses.

value.title: Blackburn warns Biden admin China is 'our adversary,' threatens supply chain
value.excerpt: EXCLUSIVE: Republican Sen. Marsha Blackburn is warning the Biden administration that China is "our adversary," saying Beijing threatens our supply chain and urging the White House to "step up their game."

value.title: Republicans tee up attacks on Biden—and Kamala Harris | Raleigh News & Observer
value.excerpt: Republicans are planning to make Vice President Kamala Harris and the Biden administration a focus of political attacks in the lead-up to the 2022 midterm elections.

value.title: House Freedom Caucus members question Liz Cheney's leadership again after her latest Trump comments
value.excerpt: House Freedom Caucus members questioned GOP conference chairwoman Liz Cheney's leadership — again — at a news conference Thursday after the Wyoming Republican congresswoman's comments that she believes former President Donald Trump shouldn't play a role in the Republican Party.

value.title: Manhattan district attorney obtains Trump's long-sought tax records
value.excerpt: The Manhattan District Attorney's Office has obtained former President Donald Trump's tax records, executing a subpoena for the long-sought documents after the Supreme Court declined to shield them from investigators earlier this week.

value.title: Harris addresses vaccine hesitancy in DC pharmacy visit
value.excerpt: Vice President Kamala Harris on Thursday visited a local pharmacy in Washington, DC, to highlight the Biden administration's retail pharmacy vaccination program and combat vaccine hesitancy.

value.title: Removing nuclear launch powers from President Biden would be 'wildly unconstitutional': Mike Lee
value.excerpt: Sen. Mike Lee R-UT. said Thursday that it is 'really weird' and 'unconstitutional' that Democrats want to change the nuclear launch code policy, which places sole power in the hands of the president.

value.title: Harris acknowledges 'righteous skepticism' over COVID-19 vaccine, but says 'it will save your life'
value.excerpt: Vice President Kamala Harris is urging Americans to get vaccinated for coronavirus while acknowledging the mistrust some have for medical research and development.

value.title: Biden, facing resistance in Congress, courts GOP governors
value.excerpt: Biden is spending at least as much time courting Republican governors as he is wooing the senators he needs to pass legislation in Washington.

value.title: Trump plots future -- and revenge -- from sunny Florida links
value.excerpt: In a South Florida war room, occupied most days by a party of one, a former President of the United States is plotting his return -- and his revenge.

value.title: McCarthy, Cheney have uncomfortable exchange with reporters over Trump speaking at CPAC
value.excerpt: House Minority Leader Kevin McCarthy and Rep. Liz Cheney, the third-ranking House GOP member, had a tense exchange with reporters Wednesday over whether former President Trump should speak at CPAC as planned this weekend.
